31 ( 29–33 ), femur 9 ( 8–9 ), basiventral femoral seta ( bv ) 6 ( 5–7 ); genu 5 ( 4–5 ), antaxial genual seta ( l″ ) 26 ( 23–28 ); tibia 7 ( 6–7 ), paraxial tibial seta ( l ′ ) 6 ( 5–7 ); tarsus 7 ( 6–7 ), paraxial fastigial tarsal seta ( ft ′ ) 15 ( 14–18 ), antaxial fastigial tarsal seta ( ft′′ ) 14 ( 14–18 ), paraxial unguinal tarsal seta ( u ′ ) 5 ( 5–6 ); tarsal empodium ( em ) 5 ( 4–5 ), divided, each branch 5 -rayed; tarsal solenidion ( ω ) 5 ( 5–6 ).
